        <!-- event title --> 
        <div id="diveventtitlearea"> 
         <h2>Raj Chetty â”€ Equality of Opportunity in America: Where Shall We Look?</h2> 
        </div>
        <!-- diveventtitlearea --> 
        <!-- event image and information --> 
        <div id="diveventinfo"> 
         <div class="image">
          <img src="http://watson.brown.edu/files/watson/styles/eventimage/public/imce/events/2015/3-2-15-Chetty-symposium-2015-poster.gif?itok=eVytF4-w" width="450" height="354" alt="">
         </div> 
         <div class="text"> 
          <div class="info"> 
           <p class="date">Monday, March 2, 2015</p> 
           <p class="time">4 p.m.</p> 
           <p class="location">Salomon Center for Teaching 001</p> 
          </div> 
          <p><em>An Economics in the Real World Event</em></p> 
          <p><a href="http://www.rajchetty.com/">Raj Chetty</a>, Bloomberg Professor of Economics, Harvard University</p> 
          <p>Comments by: John Friedman, Justine Hastings, and Glenn Loury, Brown Department of Economics.</p> 
          <p>Professor Chetty is widely viewed as one of the most influential young economists in the United States and is a recipient of a MacArthur Foundation grant and the American Economic Associationâ€™s John Bates Clark Medal. Much of his recent research concerns equality of opportunity. The entire Brown community, especially undergraduates regardless of concentration, are encouraged to attend.</p> 
          <p class="sponsor">Co-sponsored by the Department of Economics and the Watson Institute.</p> 
         </div> 
        </div>
